mscLpEnetCidDataTable.name: mscLpEnetCidDataTable
mscLpEnetCidDataTable.description: This group contains the attribute for a component's Customer Identifier (CID). Refer to the attribute description for a detailed explanation of CIDs.

mscLpEnetCustomerIdentifier.name: mscLpEnetCustomerIdentifier
mscLpEnetCustomerIdentifier.description: This attribute holds the Customer Identifier (CID). Every component has a CID. If a component has a cid attribute, the component's CID is the provisioned value of that attribute; otherwise the component inherits the CID of its parent. The top- level component has a CID of 0. Every operator session also has a CID, which is the CID provisioned for the operator's user ID. An operator will see only the stream data for components having a matching CID. Also, the operator will be allowed to issue commands for only those components which have a matching CID. An operator CID of 0 is used to identify the Network Manager (referred to as 'NetMan' in DPN). This CID matches the CID of any component. Values 1 to 8191 inclusive (equivalent to 'basic CIDs' in DPN) may be assigned to specific customers.

mscLpEnetIfEntryTable.name: mscLpEnetIfEntryTable
mscLpEnetIfEntryTable.description: This group contains the provisionable attributes for the ifEntry.

mscLpEnetIfAdminStatus.name: mscLpEnetIfAdminStatus
mscLpEnetIfAdminStatus.description: The desired state of the interface. The up state indicates the interface is operational. The down state indicates the interface is not operational. The testing state indicates that no operational packets can be passed.

mscLpEnetIfIndex.name: mscLpEnetIfIndex
mscLpEnetIfIndex.description: This is the index for the IfEntry. Its value is automatically initialized during the provisioning process.

mscLpEnetProvTable.name: mscLpEnetProvTable
mscLpEnetProvTable.description: This group contains provisioned attributes for the Ethernet component.

mscLpEnetHeartbeatPacket.name: mscLpEnetHeartbeatPacket
mscLpEnetHeartbeatPacket.description: The heartbeat packet feature is used to select whether or not the station will generate a heartbeat packet. If enabled, the station will generate one heartbeat packet every second. If disabled, the station will not generate any heartbeat packets.

mscLpEnetApplicationFramerName.name: mscLpEnetApplicationFramerName
mscLpEnetApplicationFramerName.description: This attribute contains the component name of a Framer which is associated with the Ethernet component. This link is used by the component administration system (CAS) to identify which card the application component (associated with the Framer component) is to be created.

mscLpEnetAdminInfoTable.name: mscLpEnetAdminInfoTable
mscLpEnetAdminInfoTable.description: This group contains the attributes pertaining to the vendor of the equipment.

mscLpEnetVendor.name: mscLpEnetVendor
mscLpEnetVendor.description: This is the name of the vendor supplying the facility.

mscLpEnetCommentText.name: mscLpEnetCommentText
mscLpEnetCommentText.description: Any miscellaneous text about the facility.

mscLpEnetStateTable.name: mscLpEnetStateTable
mscLpEnetStateTable.description: This group contains the three OSI State attributes. The descriptions generically indicate what each state attribute implies about the component. Note that not all the values and state combinations described here are supported by every component which uses this group. For component-specific information and the valid state combinations, refer to NTP 241-7001-150, Passport Operations and Maintenance Guide.

mscLpEnetAdminState.name: mscLpEnetAdminState
mscLpEnetAdminState.description: This attribute indicates the OSI Administrative State of the component. The value locked indicates that the component is administratively prohibited from providing services for its users. A Lock or Lock - force command has been previously issued for this component. When the value is locked, the value of usageState must be idle. The value shuttingDown indicates that the component is administratively permitted to provide service to its existing users only. A Lock command was issued against the component and it is in the process of shutting down. The value unlocked indicates that the component is administratively permitted to provide services for its users. To enter this state, issue an Unlock command to this component.

mscLpEnetOperationalState.name: mscLpEnetOperationalState
mscLpEnetOperationalState.description: This attribute indicates the OSI Operational State of the component. The value enabled indicates that the component is available for operation. Note that if adminState is locked, it would still not be providing service. The value disabled indicates that the component is not available for operation. For example, something is wrong with the component itself, or with another component on which this one depends. If the value is disabled, the usageState must be idle.

mscLpEnetUsageState.name: mscLpEnetUsageState
mscLpEnetUsageState.description: This attribute indicates the OSI Usage State of the component. The value idle indicates that the component is not currently in use. The value active indicates that the component is in use and has spare capacity to provide for additional users. The value busy indicates that the component is in use and has no spare operating capacity for additional users at this time.

mscLpEnetOperStatusTable.name: mscLpEnetOperStatusTable
mscLpEnetOperStatusTable.description: This group includes the Operational Status attribute. This attribute defines the current operational state of this component.

mscLpEnetSnmpOperStatus.name: mscLpEnetSnmpOperStatus
mscLpEnetSnmpOperStatus.description: The current state of the interface. The up state indicates the interface is operational and capable of forwarding packets. The down state indicates the interface is not operational, thus unable to forward packets. testing state indicates that no operational packets can be passed.

mscLpEnetOperTable.name: mscLpEnetOperTable
mscLpEnetOperTable.description: This group contains the operational attributes of the Ethernet component.

mscLpEnetMacAddress.name: mscLpEnetMacAddress
mscLpEnetMacAddress.description: The medium access controller (MAC) address is an address that is only recognized by one station on the network The value of this attribute will be assigned by the system. MAC address is displayed in canonical format.

mscLpEnetStatsTable.name: mscLpEnetStatsTable
mscLpEnetStatsTable.description: This group contains statistical attributes for the Ethernet component.

mscLpEnetAlignmentErrors.name: mscLpEnetAlignmentErrors
mscLpEnetAlignmentErrors.description: The alignmentErrors counter indicates the number of frames received which were not an integral number of octets in length. Frames will be checked for alignmentErrors before they are checked for Frame Check Sequence (FCS) errors. If there is an alignment error, the error will only be counted here and not in fcsErrors. This counter wraps around after it exceeds its maximum value.

mscLpEnetFcsErrors.name: mscLpEnetFcsErrors
mscLpEnetFcsErrors.description: The fcsErrors, Frame Check Sequence (FCS) error, counter indicates the number of frames received which were an integral number of octets in length and did not pass the FCS check. This counter wraps around after it exceeds its maximum value.

mscLpEnetSingleCollisionFrames.name: mscLpEnetSingleCollisionFrames
mscLpEnetSingleCollisionFrames.description: The singleCollisionFrames counter indicates the number of frames successfully transmitted which experienced exactly one collision. This counter wraps around after it exceeds its maximum value.

mscLpEnetMultipleCollisionFrames.name: mscLpEnetMultipleCollisionFrames
mscLpEnetMultipleCollisionFrames.description: The multipleCollisionFrames counter indicates the number of frames successfully transmitted which experienced more than one collision. This counter wraps around after it exceeds its maximum value.

mscLpEnetSqeTestErrors.name: mscLpEnetSqeTestErrors
mscLpEnetSqeTestErrors.description: The sqeTestErrors, Signal Quality Error (SQE) Test errors, counter indicates the number of times the 'SQE Test Error' message has been generated for the station. This counter wraps around after it exceeds its maximum value.

mscLpEnetDeferredTransmissions.name: mscLpEnetDeferredTransmissions
mscLpEnetDeferredTransmissions.description: The deferredTransmissions counter indicates the number of frames which experienced a transmission delay because the medium was busy. This counter wraps around after it exceeds its maximum value.

mscLpEnetLateCollisions.name: mscLpEnetLateCollisions
mscLpEnetLateCollisions.description: The lateCollisions counter indicates the number of times a collision was detected later than 512 bit-times into the transmission of a packet. This counter wraps around after it exceeds its maximum value.

mscLpEnetExcessiveCollisions.name: mscLpEnetExcessiveCollisions
mscLpEnetExcessiveCollisions.description: The excessiveCollisions counter indicates the number of frames which failed to get transmitted due to excessive collisions. This counter wraps around after it exceeds its maximum value.

mscLpEnetMacTransmitErrors.name: mscLpEnetMacTransmitErrors
mscLpEnetMacTransmitErrors.description: The Medium Access Controller (MAC) transmit error counter indicates the number of times that a transmission failed due to internal MAC transmit errors. This counter wraps around after it exceeds its maximum value.

mscLpEnetCarrierSenseErrors.name: mscLpEnetCarrierSenseErrors
mscLpEnetCarrierSenseErrors.description: The carrier sense error counter indicates the number of times that the carrier sense condition was lost or never asserted when attempting to transmit a frame. This counter wraps around after it exceeds its maximum value.

mscLpEnetFrameTooLongs.name: mscLpEnetFrameTooLongs
mscLpEnetFrameTooLongs.description: The frame too long counter indicates the number of frames received which exceeded the maximum frame size. This counter wraps around after it exceeds its maximum value.

mscLpEnetMacReceiveErrors.name: mscLpEnetMacReceiveErrors
mscLpEnetMacReceiveErrors.description: The Medium Access Controller (MAC) receive error counter indicates the number of times a receive failed due to internal MAC receive errors. This counter wraps around after it exceeds its maximum value.

mscLpEnetTestPTOTable.description: This group contains the operational data for the LanPortTest component.

mscLpEnetTestType.name: mscLpEnetTestType
mscLpEnetTestType.description: This attribute is the type of test to be run. The available test types include the following: card test sets up an internal loop on the board and runs a bit error rate test; manual test assumes the line is looped back externally and a bit error rate test is performed; localLoop test loops back the local modem and performs a bit error rate test; remoteLoop test loops back the remote modem (or CSU) and performs a bit error rate test; externalLoop test loops back the line to the far end; payloadLoop test only loops back the payload data received from the incoming line; Note that localLoop, remoteLoop and payloadLoop are not supported by all function processors.

mscLpEnetTestFrmSize.name: mscLpEnetTestFrmSize
mscLpEnetTestFrmSize.description: This attribute defines the size of the test data frames in number of bytes.

mscLpEnetTestDuration.name: mscLpEnetTestDuration
mscLpEnetTestDuration.description: This attribute is the duration (in minutes) that test data will be transmitted. In the case of an externalLoop, this is the time that the loop is in effect. Note that dataStartDelay does not apply to the externalLoop.

mscLpEnetTestResultsTable.name: mscLpEnetTestResultsTable
mscLpEnetTestResultsTable.description: This group contains all the statistics related attributes of the Test component.

mscLpEnetTestElapsedTime.name: mscLpEnetTestElapsedTime
mscLpEnetTestElapsedTime.description: This attribute is the number of minutes elapsed since the test started for an externalLoop test. For a data test, this is the time since test data was first transmitted.

mscLpEnetTestTimeRemaining.name: mscLpEnetTestTimeRemaining
mscLpEnetTestTimeRemaining.description: This attribute is the number of minutes remaining before the test is to be stopped according to the duration attribute.

mscLpEnetTestCauseOfTermination.name: mscLpEnetTestCauseOfTermination
mscLpEnetTestCauseOfTermination.description: This attribute records the reason the test is terminated.

mscLpEnetTestFrmTx.name: mscLpEnetTestFrmTx
mscLpEnetTestFrmTx.description: This attribute is the total number of frames sent during the test period. This counter is not expected to reach its maximum value.

mscLpEnetTestBitsTx.name: mscLpEnetTestBitsTx
mscLpEnetTestBitsTx.description: This attribute is the total number of bits sent during the test period. This counter is not expected to reach its maximum value.

mscLpEnetTestFrmRx.name: mscLpEnetTestFrmRx
mscLpEnetTestFrmRx.description: This attribute is the total number of frames received during the test period. This counter is not expected to reach its maximum value. The counter will wrap around to 0 if it does reach its maximum value.

mscLpEnetTestBitsRx.name: mscLpEnetTestBitsRx
mscLpEnetTestBitsRx.description: This attribute is the total number of bits received during the test period. This counter is not expected to reach its maximum value. The counter will wrap around to 0 if it does reach its maximum value.

mscLpEnetTestErroredFrmRx.name: mscLpEnetTestErroredFrmRx
mscLpEnetTestErroredFrmRx.description: This attribute is the total number of errored frames received during the test period. This counter is not expected to reach its maximum value. The counter will wrap around to 0 if it does reach its maximum value.

mscLpFiCidDataTable.name: mscLpFiCidDataTable
mscLpFiCidDataTable.description: This group contains the attribute for a component's Customer Identifier (CID). Refer to the attribute description for a detailed explanation of CIDs.

mscLpFiCustomerIdentifier.name: mscLpFiCustomerIdentifier
mscLpFiCustomerIdentifier.description: This attribute holds the Customer Identifier (CID). Every component has a CID. If a component has a cid attribute, the component's CID is the provisioned value of that attribute; otherwise the component inherits the CID of its parent. The top- level component has a CID of 0. Every operator session also has a CID, which is the CID provisioned for the operator's user ID. An operator will see only the stream data for components having a matching CID. Also, the operator will be allowed to issue commands for only those components which have a matching CID. An operator CID of 0 is used to identify the Network Manager (referred to as 'NetMan' in DPN). This CID matches the CID of any component. Values 1 to 8191 inclusive (equivalent to 'basic CIDs' in DPN) may be assigned to specific customers.

mscLpFiIfEntryTable.name: mscLpFiIfEntryTable
mscLpFiIfEntryTable.description: This group contains the provisionable attributes for the ifEntry.

mscLpFiIfAdminStatus.name: mscLpFiIfAdminStatus
mscLpFiIfAdminStatus.description: The desired state of the interface. The up state indicates the interface is operational. The down state indicates the interface is not operational. The testing state indicates that no operational packets can be passed.

mscLpFiIfIndex.name: mscLpFiIfIndex
mscLpFiIfIndex.description: This is the index for the IfEntry. Its value is automatically initialized during the provisioning process.

mscLpFiSmtProvTable.name: mscLpFiSmtProvTable
mscLpFiSmtProvTable.description: This group contains the provisionable Station Management (SMT) attributes of the Fddi component.

mscLpFiUserData.name: mscLpFiUserData
mscLpFiUserData.description: The user data field is used to identify the FDDI interface on the ring. The user data contains a message with a maximum of 32 characters.

mscLpFiAcceptAa.name: mscLpFiAcceptAa
mscLpFiAcceptAa.description: The acceptAa attribute defines the station type A to station type A connection policy. If enabled, the connection will be accepted. If disabled, the connection will be rejected.

mscLpFiAcceptBb.name: mscLpFiAcceptBb
mscLpFiAcceptBb.description: The acceptBb attribute defines the station type B to station type B connection policy. If enabled, the connection will be accepted. If disabled, the connection will be rejected.

mscLpFiAcceptAs.name: mscLpFiAcceptAs
mscLpFiAcceptAs.description: The acceptAs attribute defines the station type A to station type S connection policy. If enabled, the connection will be accepted. If disabled, the connection will be rejected.

mscLpFiAcceptBs.name: mscLpFiAcceptBs
mscLpFiAcceptBs.description: The acceptBs attribute defines the station type B to station type S connection policy. If enabled, the connection will be accepted. If disabled, the connection will be rejected.

mscLpFiAcceptAm.name: mscLpFiAcceptAm
mscLpFiAcceptAm.description: The acceptAm attribute defines the station type A to station type M connection policy. If enabled, the connection will be accepted. If disabled, the connection will be rejected.

mscLpFiAcceptBm.name: mscLpFiAcceptBm
mscLpFiAcceptBm.description: The acceptBm attribute defines the station type B to station type M connection policy. If enabled, the connection will be accepted. If disabled, the connection will be rejected.

mscLpFiUseThruBa.name: mscLpFiUseThruBa
mscLpFiUseThruBa.description: The useThruBa attribute is used to configure the requested path of the associated station. If enabled, only the secondary preferred path is permitted. If disabled, only the primary preferred path is permitted.

mscLpFiNeighborNotifyInterval.name: mscLpFiNeighborNotifyInterval
mscLpFiNeighborNotifyInterval.description: The neighborNotifyInterval attribute contains the amount of time, expressed in seconds, between neighbor notification frames.

mscLpFiStatusReportPolicy.name: mscLpFiStatusReportPolicy
mscLpFiStatusReportPolicy.description: The statusReportPolicy attribute indicates whether or not the station will generate status reporting frames for its implemented events and conditions. If true, the station will generate the status frames. If false, the station will not generate the status frames.

mscLpFiTraceMaxExpirationTimer.name: mscLpFiTraceMaxExpirationTimer
mscLpFiTraceMaxExpirationTimer.description: The traceMaxExpirationTimer attribute is used to configure the maximum propagation time, expressed in milliseconds, for a trace on a FDDI topology. This value places a lower bound on the detection time for an unrecovered ring.

mscLpFiApplicationFramerName.name: mscLpFiApplicationFramerName
mscLpFiApplicationFramerName.description: This attribute contains the component name of a Framer which is associated with the Fddi component. This defines which LanApplication/n Framer will be using this Fddi interface.

mscLpFiMacProvTable.name: mscLpFiMacProvTable
mscLpFiMacProvTable.description: This group contains the provisionable MAC attributes of the Fddi component.

mscLpFiTokenRequestTimer.name: mscLpFiTokenRequestTimer
mscLpFiTokenRequestTimer.description: The tokenRequestTimer value contains the token request value assigned to the associated medium access controller (MAC). Warning: Changes to this attribute can have adverse effects on the performance of the FDDI ring. Therefore it is recommended that this parameter only be modified by personnel with a thorough understanding of the consequences that may result from changes to this attribute.

mscLpFiTokenMaxTimer.name: mscLpFiTokenMaxTimer
mscLpFiTokenMaxTimer.description: The tokenMaxTimer value is the maximum timer value the negotiated token rotation time may assume. Warning: Changes to this attribute can have adverse effects on the performance of the FDDI ring. Therefore it is recommended that this parameter only be modified by personnel with a thorough understanding of the consequences that may result from changes to this attribute.

mscLpFiValidTransmissionTimer.name: mscLpFiValidTransmissionTimer
mscLpFiValidTransmissionTimer.description: The validTransmissionTimer (Tvx) value specifies the amount of time required for a valid transmission. The station must receive a valid transmission once every Tvx. Warning: Changes to this attribute can have adverse effects on the performance of the FDDI ring. Therefore it is recommended that this parameter only be modified by personnel with a thorough understanding of the consequences that may result from changes to this attribute.

mscLpFiAdminInfoTable.name: mscLpFiAdminInfoTable
mscLpFiAdminInfoTable.description: This group contains the attributes pertaining to the vendor of the equipment.

mscLpFiVendor.name: mscLpFiVendor
mscLpFiVendor.description: This is the name of the vendor supplying the facility.

mscLpFiCommentText.name: mscLpFiCommentText
mscLpFiCommentText.description: Any miscellaneous text about the facility.

mscLpFiStateTable.name: mscLpFiStateTable
mscLpFiStateTable.description: This group contains the three OSI State attributes. The descriptions generically indicate what each state attribute implies about the component. Note that not all the values and state combinations described here are supported by every component which uses this group. For component-specific information and the valid state combinations, refer to NTP 241-7001-150, Passport Operations and Maintenance Guide.

mscLpFiAdminState.name: mscLpFiAdminState
mscLpFiAdminState.description: This attribute indicates the OSI Administrative State of the component. The value locked indicates that the component is administratively prohibited from providing services for its users. A Lock or Lock - force command has been previously issued for this component. When the value is locked, the value of usageState must be idle. The value shuttingDown indicates that the component is administratively permitted to provide service to its existing users only. A Lock command was issued against the component and it is in the process of shutting down. The value unlocked indicates that the component is administratively permitted to provide services for its users. To enter this state, issue an Unlock command to this component.

mscLpFiOperationalState.name: mscLpFiOperationalState
mscLpFiOperationalState.description: This attribute indicates the OSI Operational State of the component. The value enabled indicates that the component is available for operation. Note that if adminState is locked, it would still not be providing service. The value disabled indicates that the component is not available for operation. For example, something is wrong with the component itself, or with another component on which this one depends. If the value is disabled, the usageState must be idle.

mscLpFiUsageState.name: mscLpFiUsageState
mscLpFiUsageState.description: This attribute indicates the OSI Usage State of the component. The value idle indicates that the component is not currently in use. The value active indicates that the component is in use and has spare capacity to provide for additional users. The value busy indicates that the component is in use and has no spare operating capacity for additional users at this time.

mscLpFiOperStatusTable.name: mscLpFiOperStatusTable
mscLpFiOperStatusTable.description: This group includes the Operational Status attribute. This attribute defines the current operational state of this component.

mscLpFiSnmpOperStatus.name: mscLpFiSnmpOperStatus
mscLpFiSnmpOperStatus.description: The current state of the interface. The up state indicates the interface is operational and capable of forwarding packets. The down state indicates the interface is not operational, thus unable to forward packets. testing state indicates that no operational packets can be passed.

mscLpFiSmtOperTable.name: mscLpFiSmtOperTable
mscLpFiSmtOperTable.description: This group contains the operational station management (SMT) attributes of the Fddi component.

mscLpFiVersion.name: mscLpFiVersion
mscLpFiVersion.description: The version attribute contains a copy of the currently supported version numbers of the management information base (MIB) and the station management (SMT).

mscLpFiBypassPresent.name: mscLpFiBypassPresent
mscLpFiBypassPresent.description: The bypassPresent attribute indicates whether the optical bypass switch is present on its AB port pair. If true, the optical bypass switch is present. If false, it is not present.

mscLpFiEcmState.name: mscLpFiEcmState
mscLpFiEcmState.description: The ecmState, Entity Coordination Manager (ECM), state indicates the current state of the ECM state machine.

mscLpFiCfState.name: mscLpFiCfState
mscLpFiCfState.description: The cfState attribute indicates the current state of the configuration management (CFM) state machine.

mscLpFiMacOperTable.name: mscLpFiMacOperTable
mscLpFiMacOperTable.description: This group contains the operational Medium Access Controller (MAC) attributes of the of the Fddi component.

mscLpFiRingLatency.name: mscLpFiRingLatency
mscLpFiRingLatency.description: The ringLatency attribute contains the measured ring latency of the ring the station is attached to.

mscLpFiMacAddress.name: mscLpFiMacAddress
mscLpFiMacAddress.description: The medium access controller (MAC) address is an address that is recognized by only one station on the attached ring. The value of this attribute is assigned by the system. This attribute is displayed in canonical format. The non-canonical version of this address is indicated in ncMacAddress.

mscLpFiUpstreamNeighbor.name: mscLpFiUpstreamNeighbor
mscLpFiUpstreamNeighbor.description: The upstreamNeighbor attribute contains the MAC address associated with the upstream neighbor station on the ring. This attribute is displayed in canonical format. The non-canonical version of this address is indicated in ncUpstreamNeighbor.

mscLpFiDownstreamNeighbor.name: mscLpFiDownstreamNeighbor
mscLpFiDownstreamNeighbor.description: The downstreamNeighbor attribute contains the MAC address associated with the downstream station on the ring. This attribute is displayed in canonical format. The non-canonical version of this address is indicated in ncDownstreamNeighbor.

mscLpFiOldUpstreamNeighbor.name: mscLpFiOldUpstreamNeighbor
mscLpFiOldUpstreamNeighbor.description: The oldUpstreamNeighbor attribute contains the previous value of the MAC address associated with the upstream station on the ring. This attribute is displayed in canonical format. The non-canonical version of this address is indicated in ncOldUpstreamNeighbor.

mscLpFiOldDownstreamNeighbor.name: mscLpFiOldDownstreamNeighbor
mscLpFiOldDownstreamNeighbor.description: The oldDownstreamNeighbor attribute contains the previous value of the MAC address associated with the downstream station on the ring. This attribute is displayed in canonical format. The non-canonical version of this address is indicated in ncOldDownstreamNeighbor.

mscLpFiDupAddressTest.name: mscLpFiDupAddressTest
mscLpFiDupAddressTest.description: The dupAddressTest attribute indicates the condition results of the duplicate address test. If notDone, the test has not been executed. If pass, the test has successfully executed. If fail, the test has failed.

mscLpFiTokenNegotiatedTimer.name: mscLpFiTokenNegotiatedTimer
mscLpFiTokenNegotiatedTimer.description: The tokenNegotiatedTimer specifies the negotiated token rotation time.

mscLpFiFrameCounts.name: mscLpFiFrameCounts
mscLpFiFrameCounts.description: The frameCounts attribute contains the number of frames that have been received by the station. This counter will wrap around after it reaches its maximum value.

mscLpFiCopiedCounts.name: mscLpFiCopiedCounts
mscLpFiCopiedCounts.description: The copiedCounts attribute contains the number of frames successfully copied into this station's receive buffers, not including MAC control frames. This counter will wrap around after it reaches its maximum value.

mscLpFiTransmitCounts.name: mscLpFiTransmitCounts
mscLpFiTransmitCounts.description: The transmitCounts attribute contains the number of frames transmitted by this station, not including MAC control frames. This counter will wrap around after it reaches its maximum value.

mscLpFiErrorCounts.name: mscLpFiErrorCounts
mscLpFiErrorCounts.description: The errorCounts attribute contains the number of error frames first detected by this station. This counter will wrap around after it reaches its maximum value.

mscLpFiLostCounts.name: mscLpFiLostCounts
mscLpFiLostCounts.description: The lostCounts attribute contains the number of instances that the station has detected a format error during frame reception such that the frame was stripped. This counter will wrap around after it reaches its maximum value.

mscLpFiRmtState.name: mscLpFiRmtState
mscLpFiRmtState.description: The rmtState, ring management (RMT), state indicates the current state of the RMT state machine.

mscLpFiFrameErrorFlag.name: mscLpFiFrameErrorFlag
mscLpFiFrameErrorFlag.description: The frameErrorFlag attribute indicates the MAC frame error condition status. If true, a MAC frame error is present. If false, a MAC frame error condition is not present.

mscLpFiMacCOperTable.name: mscLpFiMacCOperTable
mscLpFiMacCOperTable.description: This group contains the operational attributes of the Medium Access Controller (MAC) Counters Table of the Fddi component.

mscLpFiTokenCounts.name: mscLpFiTokenCounts
mscLpFiTokenCounts.description: The tokenCounts attribute contains the number of times the station has received a token. This counter will wrap around after it reaches its maximum value.

mscLpFiTvxExpiredCounts.name: mscLpFiTvxExpiredCounts
mscLpFiTvxExpiredCounts.description: The tvxExpiredCounts, Transmission Valid eXpired (TVX), attribute contains the number of times that TVX timer has expired. This counter may increment as stations go on and off the ring. A rapidly increasing value may indicate a problem. This counter will wrap around after it reaches its maximum value.

mscLpFiNotCopiedCounts.name: mscLpFiNotCopiedCounts
mscLpFiNotCopiedCounts.description: The notCopiedCounts attribute contains the number of times that the station has detected a frame addressed to itself but did not copy it due to local buffer congestion. This counter will wrap around after it reaches its maximum value.

mscLpFiLateCounts.name: mscLpFiLateCounts
mscLpFiLateCounts.description: The lateCounts attribute contains the number of token rotation time (TRT) expirations since the station was reset or a token was received. This counter may increment as stations go on and off the ring. A rapidly increasing value may indicate a problem. This counter will wrap around after it reaches its maximum value.

mscLpFiRingOpCounts.name: mscLpFiRingOpCounts
mscLpFiRingOpCounts.description: The ringOpCounts attribute contains the number of times the station has made the transition from the ring not operational state to the ring operational state.

mscLpFiNcMacAddress.name: mscLpFiNcMacAddress
mscLpFiNcMacAddress.description: The medium access controller (MAC) address is an address that is recognized by only one station on the attached ring. mscLpFiPhyProvTable.description: This group contains the provisionable attributes of the Fddi Phy component.

mscLpFiPhyLerCutoff.name: mscLpFiPhyLerCutoff
mscLpFiPhyLerCutoff.description: The lerCutoff attribute contains the link error rate estimate at which a link connection will be broken. The values will range from 10**-4 to 10**-15. Only the absolute value of the base 10 log is reported.

mscLpFiPhyLerAlarm.name: mscLpFiPhyLerAlarm
mscLpFiPhyLerAlarm.description: The lerAlarm attribute contains the link error rate estimate at which a link connection will generate an alarm. The values will range from 10**-4 to 10**-15. Only the absolute value of the base 10 log is reported

mscLpFiPhyLinkErrorMonitor.name: mscLpFiPhyLinkErrorMonitor
mscLpFiPhyLinkErrorMonitor.description: The linkErrorMonitor attribute is used to select the state of the link error monitor for the associated Phy component. If enabled, the link error monitor will send the correct test status to the neighboring station. If disabled, the link error monitor will always send a test passed status to the neighboring station.

mscLpFiPhyOperTable.name: mscLpFiPhyOperTable
mscLpFiPhyOperTable.description: This group contains the operational attributes of the Fddi Phy component.

mscLpFiPhyNeighborType.name: mscLpFiPhyNeighborType
mscLpFiPhyNeighborType.description: This attribute indicates the neighbor type of the neighbor physical layer.

mscLpFiPhyLctFailCounts.name: mscLpFiPhyLctFailCounts
mscLpFiPhyLctFailCounts.description: The lctFailCounts attribute contains the number of consecutive times the Link Confidence Test (LCT) has failed. This counter will wrap around after it reaches its maximum value.

mscLpFiPhyLerEstimate.name: mscLpFiPhyLerEstimate
mscLpFiPhyLerEstimate.description: The lerEstimate attribute contains a long term average link error rate. The values will range from 10**-4 to 10**-15. Only the absolute value of the base 10 log is reported

mscLpFiPhyLemRejectCounts.name: mscLpFiPhyLemRejectCounts
mscLpFiPhyLemRejectCounts.description: The lemRejectCounts attribute contains the number of times that a link has been rejected. This counter will wrap around after it reaches its maximum value.

mscLpFiPhyLemCounts.name: mscLpFiPhyLemCounts
mscLpFiPhyLemCounts.description: The lemCounts attribute contains the aggregate link error monitor error count. This counter is set to zero only on station initialization. This counter will wrap around after it reaches its maximum value.

mscLpFiPhyPcmState.name: mscLpFiPhyPcmState
mscLpFiPhyPcmState.description: The pcmState, physical connection manager (PCM), state indicates the current state of the PCM state machine.

mscLpFiPhyLerFlag.name: mscLpFiPhyLerFlag
mscLpFiPhyLerFlag.description: The lerFlag attribute indicates when the link error rate estimate is less than or equal to the link error rate alarm. If true, the value of the link error rate estimate is less than or equal to the link error rate alarm. If false, the value of the link error rate estimate is greater than the link error rate alarm.

mscLpFiPhySignalState.name: mscLpFiPhySignalState
mscLpFiPhySignalState.description: The signalState attribute contains the current physical connection manager (PCM) signal bit being transmitted, or was transmitted, during the PCM signal state.

mscLpFiPhySignalBitsRcvd.name: mscLpFiPhySignalBitsRcvd
mscLpFiPhySignalBitsRcvd.description: The signalBitsRcvd attribute contains the current physical connection manager (PCM) signal bits received. Description of bits: escape(0) phyTypeL(1) phyTypeH(2) accept(3) lctLengthL(4) lctLengthH(5) macAvail(6) lctResult(7) macLoop(8) macOnPhy(9)

mscLpFiPhySignalBitsTxmt.name: mscLpFiPhySignalBitsTxmt
mscLpFiPhySignalBitsTxmt.description: The signalBitsTxmt attribute contains the current physical connection manager (PCM) signal bits transmitted. Description of bits: escape(0) phyTypeL(1) phyTypeH(2) accept(3) lctLengthL(4) lctLengthH(5) macAvail(6) lctResult(7) macLoop(8) macOnPhy(9)

mscLpFiTestRowStatusEntry.description: A single entry in the table represents a single mscLpFiTest component.

mscLpFiTestRowStatus.description: This variable is used as the basis for SNMP naming of mscLpFiTest components. These components cannot be added nor deleted.

mscLpFiTestComponentName.description: This variable provides the component's string name for use with the ASCII Console Interface

mscLpFiTestStorageType.name: mscLpFiTestStorageType
mscLpFiTestStorageType.description: This variable represents the storage type value for the mscLpFiTest tables.

mscLpFiTestIndex.description: This variable represents the index for the mscLpFiTest tables.

mscLpFiTestPTOTable.name: mscLpFiTestPTOTable
mscLpFiTestPTOTable.description: This group contains the operational data for the LanPortTest component.

mscLpFiTestType.name: mscLpFiTestType
mscLpFiTestType.description: This attribute is the type of test to be run. The available test types include the following: card test sets up an internal loop on the board and runs a bit error rate test; manual test assumes the line is looped back externally and a bit error rate test is performed; localLoop test loops back the local modem and performs a bit error rate test; remoteLoop test loops back the remote modem (or CSU) and performs a bit error rate test; externalLoop test loops back the line to the far end; payloadLoop test only loops back the payload data received from the incoming line; Note that localLoop, remoteLoop and payloadLoop are not supported by all function processors.

mscLpFiTestFrmSize.name: mscLpFiTestFrmSize
mscLpFiTestFrmSize.description: This attribute defines the size of the test data frames in number of bytes.

mscLpFiTestDuration.name: mscLpFiTestDuration
mscLpFiTestDuration.description: This attribute is the duration (in minutes) that test data will be transmitted. In the case of an externalLoop, this is the time that the loop is in effect. Note that dataStartDelay does not apply to the externalLoop.

mscLpFiTestResultsTable.name: mscLpFiTestResultsTable
mscLpFiTestResultsTable.description: This group contains all the statistics related attributes of the Test component.

mscLpFiTestElapsedTime.name: mscLpFiTestElapsedTime
mscLpFiTestElapsedTime.description: This attribute is the number of minutes elapsed since the test started for an externalLoop test. For a data test, this is the time since test data was first transmitted.

mscLpFiTestTimeRemaining.name: mscLpFiTestTimeRemaining
mscLpFiTestTimeRemaining.description: This attribute is the number of minutes remaining before the test is to be stopped according to the duration attribute.

mscLpFiTestCauseOfTermination.name: mscLpFiTestCauseOfTermination
mscLpFiTestCauseOfTermination.description: This attribute records the reason the test is terminated.

mscLpFiTestFrmTx.name: mscLpFiTestFrmTx
mscLpFiTestFrmTx.description: This attribute is the total number of frames sent during the test period. This counter is not expected to reach its maximum value.

mscLpFiTestBitsTx.name: mscLpFiTestBitsTx
mscLpFiTestBitsTx.description: This attribute is the total number of bits sent during the test period. This counter is not expected to reach its maximum value.

mscLpFiTestFrmRx.name: mscLpFiTestFrmRx
mscLpFiTestFrmRx.description: This attribute is the total number of frames received during the test period. This counter is not expected to reach its maximum value. The counter will wrap around to 0 if it does reach its maximum value.

mscLpFiTestBitsRx.name: mscLpFiTestBitsRx
mscLpFiTestBitsRx.description: This attribute is the total number of bits received during the test period. This counter is not expected to reach its maximum value. The counter will wrap around to 0 if it does reach its maximum value.

mscLpFiTestErroredFrmRx.name: mscLpFiTestErroredFrmRx
mscLpFiTestErroredFrmRx.description: This attribute is the total number of errored frames received during the test period. This counter is not expected to reach its maximum value. The counter will wrap around to 0 if it does reach its maximum value.

mscLpTrComponentName.description: This variable provides the component's string name for use with the ASCII Console Interface

mscLpTrIndex.description: This variable represents the index for the mscLpTr tables.

mscLpTrCidDataTable.name: mscLpTrCidDataTable
mscLpTrCidDataTable.description: This group contains the attribute for a component's Customer Identifier (CID). Refer to the attribute description for a detailed explanation of CIDs.

mscLpTrCustomerIdentifier.name: mscLpTrCustomerIdentifier
mscLpTrCustomerIdentifier.description: This attribute holds the Customer Identifier (CID). Every component has a CID. If a component has a cid attribute, the component's CID is the provisioned value of that attribute; otherwise the component inherits the CID of its parent. The top- level component has a CID of 0. Every operator session also has a CID, which is the CID provisioned for the operator's user ID. An operator will see only the stream data for components having a matching CID. Also, the operator will be allowed to issue commands for only those components which have a matching CID. An operator CID of 0 is used to identify the Network Manager (referred to as 'NetMan' in DPN). This CID matches the CID of any component. Values 1 to 8191 inclusive (equivalent to 'basic CIDs' in DPN) may be assigned to specific customers.

mscLpTrIfEntryTable.name: mscLpTrIfEntryTable
mscLpTrIfEntryTable.description: This group contains the provisionable attributes for the ifEntry.

mscLpTrIfAdminStatus.name: mscLpTrIfAdminStatus
mscLpTrIfAdminStatus.description: The desired state of the interface. The up state indicates the interface is operational. The down state indicates the interface is not operational. The testing state indicates that no operational packets can be passed.

mscLpTrIfIndex.name: mscLpTrIfIndex
mscLpTrIfIndex.description: This is the index for the IfEntry. Its value is automatically initialized during the provisioning process.

mscLpTrProvTable.name: mscLpTrProvTable
mscLpTrProvTable.description: This group contains the provisionable attributes of the Token Ring port.

mscLpTrRingSpeed.name: mscLpTrRingSpeed
mscLpTrRingSpeed.description: This attribute indicates the ring speed at the next insertion into the ring. Note that all the interfaces on a ring must operate at the same speed.

mscLpTrMonitorParticipate.name: mscLpTrMonitorParticipate
mscLpTrMonitorParticipate.description: This attribute determines whether the interface will participate in the active monitor selection process.

mscLpTrFunctionalAddress.name: mscLpTrFunctionalAddress
mscLpTrFunctionalAddress.description: This attribute contains a bit mask of all token ring functional addresses for which this interface will accept frames. The address is displayed in canonical form.

mscLpTrNodeAddress.name: mscLpTrNodeAddress
mscLpTrNodeAddress.description: This attribute identifies the primary, node specific address recognized by this interface. If an operator does not provision a MAC address, the interface will use a predefined, permanently assigned address. A valid node address must not be any of the following: a broadcast address, a group address, a functional address or a null address. A node address should be entered in the canonical form.

mscLpTrGroupAddress.name: mscLpTrGroupAddress
mscLpTrGroupAddress.description: This attribute identifies the group address for which this interface will accept frames. The address is displayed in canonical form. For a valid group address, the least significant bit of the first octet should be set to 1. Currently, only one group address can be provisioned for one interface.

mscLpTrProductId.name: mscLpTrProductId
mscLpTrProductId.description: This attribute is used to identify the host system attached to this interface. This information is transmitted in response to Request Station Attachment MAC frames.

mscLpTrApplicationFramerName.name: mscLpTrApplicationFramerName
mscLpTrApplicationFramerName.description: This attribute contains the component name of a Framer which is associated with the Tr component.

mscLpTrAdminInfoTable.name: mscLpTrAdminInfoTable
mscLpTrAdminInfoTable.description: This group contains the attributes pertaining to the vendor of the equipment.

mscLpTrVendor.name: mscLpTrVendor
mscLpTrVendor.description: This is the name of the vendor supplying the facility.

mscLpTrCommentText.name: mscLpTrCommentText
mscLpTrCommentText.description: Any miscellaneous text about the facility.

mscLpTrStateTable.name: mscLpTrStateTable
mscLpTrStateTable.description: This group contains the three OSI State attributes. The descriptions generically indicate what each state attribute implies about the component. Note that not all the values and state combinations described here are supported by every component which uses this group. For component-specific information and the valid state combinations, refer to NTP 241-7001-150, Passport Operations and Maintenance Guide.

mscLpTrAdminState.name: mscLpTrAdminState
mscLpTrAdminState.description: This attribute indicates the OSI Administrative State of the component. The value locked indicates that the component is administratively prohibited from providing services for its users. A Lock or Lock - force command has been previously issued for this component. When the value is locked, the value of usageState must be idle. The value shuttingDown indicates that the component is administratively permitted to provide service to its existing users only. A Lock command was issued against the component and it is in the process of shutting down. The value unlocked indicates that the component is administratively permitted to provide services for its users. To enter this state, issue an Unlock command to this component.

mscLpTrOperationalState.name: mscLpTrOperationalState
mscLpTrOperationalState.description: This attribute indicates the OSI Operational State of the component. The value enabled indicates that the component is available for operation. Note that if adminState is locked, it would still not be providing service. The value disabled indicates that the component is not available for operation. For example, something is wrong with the component itself, or with another component on which this one depends. If the value is disabled, the usageState must be idle.

mscLpTrUsageState.name: mscLpTrUsageState
mscLpTrUsageState.description: This attribute indicates the OSI Usage State of the component. The value idle indicates that the component is not currently in use. The value active indicates that the component is in use and has spare capacity to provide for additional users. The value busy indicates that the component is in use and has no spare operating capacity for additional users at this time.

mscLpTrOperStatusTable.name: mscLpTrOperStatusTable
mscLpTrOperStatusTable.description: This group includes the Operational Status attribute. This attribute defines the current operational state of this component.

mscLpTrSnmpOperStatus.name: mscLpTrSnmpOperStatus
mscLpTrSnmpOperStatus.description: The current state of the interface. The up state indicates the interface is operational and capable of forwarding packets. The down state indicates the interface is not operational, thus unable to forward packets. testing state indicates that no operational packets can be passed.

mscLpTrOperTable.name: mscLpTrOperTable
mscLpTrOperTable.description: This group contains the operational attributes of the Token Ring component.

mscLpTrMacAddress.name: mscLpTrMacAddress
mscLpTrMacAddress.description: This attribute contains the actual MAC address. The value is assigned by the system if nodeAddress is not provisioned. This address is displayed in canonical form. The non-canonical version of this address is indicated in ncMacAddress.

mscLpTrRingState.name: mscLpTrRingState
mscLpTrRingState.description: This attribute contains the value of the current interface state with respect to entering or leaving the ring.

mscLpTrRingStatus.name: mscLpTrRingStatus
mscLpTrRingStatus.description: This attribute contains the value of the current interface status after the station has entered the ring. The value is a sum of values, one for each currently applicable condition. Before the station attempts an open this attribute has the value of noStatus. noProblems = 0, ringRecovery = 32, singleStation = 64, removeReceived = 256, reserved = 512, autoRemovalError = 1024, lobeWireFault = 2048, transmitBeacon = 4096, softError = 8192, hardError = 16384, signalLoss = 32768, noStatus = 131072 Description of bits: noProblems(0) notused1(1) notused2(2) notused3(3) notused4(4) ringRecovery(5) singleStation(6) notused7(7) removeReceived(8) reserved(9) autoRemovalError(10) lobeWireFault(11) transmitBeacon(12) softError(13) hardError(14) signalLoss(15) notused16(16) noStatus(17)

mscLpTrRingOpenStatus.name: mscLpTrRingOpenStatus
mscLpTrRingOpenStatus.description: This attribute indicates what happened the last time the station attempted to enter into the ring.

mscLpTrUpStream.name: mscLpTrUpStream
mscLpTrUpStream.description: This attribute is the MAC address of the station's up-stream neighbor. This address is displayed in canonical form. The non- canonical version of this address is indicated in ncUpStream.

mscLpTrChipSet.name: mscLpTrChipSet
mscLpTrChipSet.description: This attribute identifies the hardware chip set in use by an interface.

mscLpTrLastTimeBeaconSent.name: mscLpTrLastTimeBeaconSent
mscLpTrLastTimeBeaconSent.description: This attribute indicates the time at which a Beacon frame was last transmitted on this interface.

mscLpTrStatsTable.name: mscLpTrStatsTable
mscLpTrStatsTable.description: This group contains statistical information for the Token Ring port.

mscLpTrLineErrors.name: mscLpTrLineErrors
mscLpTrLineErrors.description: This attribute contains the number of frames or tokens copied or repeated by a station where there is a non-data bit or a FCS error. This counter wraps around when the maximum value is reached.

mscLpTrBurstErrors.name: mscLpTrBurstErrors
mscLpTrBurstErrors.description: This attribute contains the number of times the station detects the absence of transitions for five consecutive half-bit times. This counter wraps around when the maximum value is reached.

mscLpTrAcErrors.name: mscLpTrAcErrors
mscLpTrAcErrors.description: This attribute contains the number of times that a station can not set the AC bits properly. This counter wraps around when the maximum value is reached.

mscLpTrAbortTransErrors.name: mscLpTrAbortTransErrors
mscLpTrAbortTransErrors.description: This attribute contains the number of aborted frames. This counter wraps around when the maximum value is reached.

mscLpTrInternalErrors.name: mscLpTrInternalErrors
mscLpTrInternalErrors.description: This attribute contains the number of internal errors. When the value of the counter soars up quickly, it indicates a potential hardware problem. This counter wraps around when the maximum value is reached.

mscLpTrLostFrameErrors.name: mscLpTrLostFrameErrors
mscLpTrLostFrameErrors.description: This attribute contains the number of times a station is transmitting and its TRR timer expires. This counter wraps around when the maximum value is reached.

mscLpTrReceiveCongestions.name: mscLpTrReceiveCongestions
mscLpTrReceiveCongestions.description: This attribute contains the number of times a station is supposed to receive a frame but cannot due to lack of buffer space. This counter wraps around when the maximum value is reached.

mscLpTrFrameCopiedErrors.name: mscLpTrFrameCopiedErrors
mscLpTrFrameCopiedErrors.description: This attribute contains the number of times a station receives a frame addressed to its specific address and detects that the A bit is set. This counter wraps around when the maximum value is reached.

mscLpTrTokenErrors.name: mscLpTrTokenErrors
mscLpTrTokenErrors.description: This attribute contains the number of times a station acting as the active monitor recognizes an error condition that needs a token transmission. This counter wraps around when the maximum value is reached.

mscLpTrSoftErrors.name: mscLpTrSoftErrors
mscLpTrSoftErrors.description: This attribute contains the number of soft errors or the number of Report Error Mac frames the station has transmitted. This counter wraps around when the maximum value is reached.

mscLpTrHardErrors.name: mscLpTrHardErrors
mscLpTrHardErrors.description: This attribute contains the number of times this interface has detected an immediately recoverable fatal error. This counter wraps around when the maximum value is reached.

mscLpTrSignalLoss.name: mscLpTrSignalLoss
mscLpTrSignalLoss.description: This attribute contains the number of times signal condition has been lost. This counter wraps around when the maximum value is reached.

mscLpTrTransmitBeacons.name: mscLpTrTransmitBeacons
mscLpTrTransmitBeacons.description: This attribute contains the number of beacon frames transmitted. This counter wraps around when the maximum value is reached.

mscLpTrRingRecoverys.name: mscLpTrRingRecoverys
mscLpTrRingRecoverys.description: This attribute contains the number of times the ring has been purged. This counter wraps around when the maximum value is reached.

mscLpTrLobeWires.name: mscLpTrLobeWires
mscLpTrLobeWires.description: This attribute contains the number of times the interface has detected a short circuit in the lobe data path. This counter wraps around when the maximum value is reached.

mscLpTrRemoveRings.name: mscLpTrRemoveRings
mscLpTrRemoveRings.description: This attribute contains the number of Remove Ring Station Mac frames received. This counter wraps around when the maximum value is reached.

mscLpTrSingleStation.name: mscLpTrSingleStation
mscLpTrSingleStation.description: This attribute contains the number of times the station has determined it is the only one on the ring. This is not necessarily an error. This counter wraps around when the maximum value is reached.

mscLpTrFreqErrors.name: mscLpTrFreqErrors
mscLpTrFreqErrors.description: This attribute contains the number of signal frequency errors detected. This counter wraps around when the maximum value is reached.

mscLpTrNcMacOperTable.name: mscLpTrNcMacOperTable

mscLpTrTestType.name: mscLpTrTestType
mscLpTrTestType.description: This attribute is the type of test to be run. The available test types include the following: card test sets up an internal loop on the board and runs a bit error rate test; manual test assumes the line is looped back externally and a bit error rate test is performed; localLoop test loops back the local modem and performs a bit error rate test; remoteLoop test loops back the remote modem (or CSU) and performs a bit error rate test; externalLoop test loops back the line to the far end; payloadLoop test only loops back the payload data received from the incoming line; Note that localLoop, remoteLoop and payloadLoop are not supported by all function processors.

mscLpTrTestFrmSize.name: mscLpTrTestFrmSize
mscLpTrTestFrmSize.description: This attribute defines the size of the test data frames in number of bytes.

mscLpTrTestDuration.name: mscLpTrTestDuration
mscLpTrTestDuration.description: This attribute is the duration (in minutes) that test data will be transmitted. In the case of an externalLoop, this is the time that the loop is in effect. Note that dataStartDelay does not apply to the externalLoop.

mscLpTrTestResultsTable.name: mscLpTrTestResultsTable
mscLpTrTestResultsTable.description: This group contains all the statistics related attributes of the Test component.

mscLpTrTestElapsedTime.name: mscLpTrTestElapsedTime
mscLpTrTestElapsedTime.description: This attribute is the number of minutes elapsed since the test started for an externalLoop test. For a data test, this is the time since test data was first transmitted.

mscLpTrTestTimeRemaining.name: mscLpTrTestTimeRemaining
mscLpTrTestTimeRemaining.description: This attribute is the number of minutes remaining before the test is to be stopped according to the duration attribute.

mscLpTrTestCauseOfTermination.name: mscLpTrTestCauseOfTermination
mscLpTrTestCauseOfTermination.description: This attribute records the reason the test is terminated.

mscLpTrTestFrmTx.name: mscLpTrTestFrmTx
mscLpTrTestFrmTx.description: This attribute is the total number of frames sent during the test period. This counter is not expected to reach its maximum value.

mscLpTrTestBitsTx.name: mscLpTrTestBitsTx
mscLpTrTestBitsTx.description: This attribute is the total number of bits sent during the test period. This counter is not expected to reach its maximum value.

mscLpTrTestFrmRx.name: mscLpTrTestFrmRx
mscLpTrTestFrmRx.description: This attribute is the total number of frames received during the test period. This counter is not expected to reach its maximum value. The counter will wrap around to 0 if it does reach its maximum value.

mscLpTrTestBitsRx.name: mscLpTrTestBitsRx
mscLpTrTestBitsRx.description: This attribute is the total number of bits received during the test period. This counter is not expected to reach its maximum value. The counter will wrap around to 0 if it does reach its maximum value.

mscLpTrTestErroredFrmRx.name: mscLpTrTestErroredFrmRx
mscLpTrTestErroredFrmRx.description: This attribute is the total number of errored frames received during the test period. This counter is not expected to reach its maximum value. The counter will wrap around to 0 if it does reach its maximum value.

mscLpIlsFwdrIfAdminStatus.name: mscLpIlsFwdrIfAdminStatus
mscLpIlsFwdrIfAdminStatus.description: The desired state of the interface. The up state indicates the interface is operational. The down state indicates the interface is not operational. The testing state indicates that no operational packets can be passed.

mscLpIlsFwdrIfIndex.name: mscLpIlsFwdrIfIndex
mscLpIlsFwdrIfIndex.description: This is the index for the IfEntry. Its value is automatically initialized during the provisioning process.

mscLpIlsFwdrStateTable.name: mscLpIlsFwdrStateTable
mscLpIlsFwdrStateTable.description: This group contains the three OSI State attributes. The descriptions generically indicate what each state attribute implies about the component. Note that not all the values and state combinations described here are supported by every component which uses this group. For component-specific information and the valid state combinations, refer to NTP 241-7001-150, Passport Operations and Maintenance Guide.

mscLpIlsFwdrAdminState.name: mscLpIlsFwdrAdminState
mscLpIlsFwdrAdminState.description: This attribute indicates the OSI Administrative State of the component. The value locked indicates that the component is administratively prohibited from providing services for its users. A Lock or Lock - force command has been previously issued for this component. When the value is locked, the value of usageState must be idle. The value shuttingDown indicates that the component is administratively permitted to provide service to its existing users only. A Lock command was issued against the component and it is in the process of shutting down. The value unlocked indicates that the component is administratively permitted to provide services for its users. To enter this state, issue an Unlock command to this component.

mscLpIlsFwdrOperationalState.name: mscLpIlsFwdrOperationalState
mscLpIlsFwdrOperationalState.description: This attribute indicates the OSI Operational State of the component. The value enabled indicates that the component is available for operation. Note that if adminState is locked, it would still not be providing service. The value disabled indicates that the component is not available for operation. For example, something is wrong with the component itself, or with another component on which this one depends. If the value is disabled, the usageState must be idle.

mscLpIlsFwdrUsageState.name: mscLpIlsFwdrUsageState
mscLpIlsFwdrUsageState.description: This attribute indicates the OSI Usage State of the component. The value idle indicates that the component is not currently in use. The value active indicates that the component is in use and has spare capacity to provide for additional users. The value busy indicates that the component is in use and has no spare operating capacity for additional users at this time.

mscLpIlsFwdrOperStatusTable.name: mscLpIlsFwdrOperStatusTable
mscLpIlsFwdrOperStatusTable.description: This group includes the Operational Status attribute. This attribute defines the current operational state of this component.

mscLpIlsFwdrSnmpOperStatus.name: mscLpIlsFwdrSnmpOperStatus
mscLpIlsFwdrSnmpOperStatus.description: The current state of the interface. The up state indicates the interface is operational and capable of forwarding packets. The down state indicates the interface is not operational, thus unable to forward packets. testing state indicates that no operational packets can be passed.

mscLpIlsFwdrStatsTable.name: mscLpIlsFwdrStatsTable

mscLpIlsFwdrFramesReceived.name: mscLpIlsFwdrFramesReceived
mscLpIlsFwdrFramesReceived.description: This attribute counts the total number of frames that have been received by this card. This counter will wrap around after it reaches its maximum value.

mscLpIlsFwdrProcessedCount.name: mscLpIlsFwdrProcessedCount
mscLpIlsFwdrProcessedCount.description: This attribute counts the number of frames successfully processed by this card. This counter will wrap around after it reaches its maximum value.

mscLpIlsFwdrErrorCount.name: mscLpIlsFwdrErrorCount
mscLpIlsFwdrErrorCount.description: This attribute counts the number of internal errors detected in transferring frames from an ATM card to this card. A continuous increment of this count indicates that the hardware may probably be defective. This counter will wrap around after it reaches its maximum value.

mscLpIlsFwdrFramesDiscarded.name: mscLpIlsFwdrFramesDiscarded
mscLpIlsFwdrFramesDiscarded.description: This attribute counts the number of frames which are discarded due to local buffer congestion. This counter will wrap around after it reaches its maximum value.

mscLpIlsFwdrTestType.name: mscLpIlsFwdrTestType
mscLpIlsFwdrTestType.description: This attribute is the type of test to be run. The available test types include the following: card test sets up an internal loop on the board and runs a bit error rate test; manual test assumes the line is looped back externally and a bit error rate test is performed; localLoop test loops back the local modem and performs a bit error rate test; remoteLoop test loops back the remote modem (or CSU) and performs a bit error rate test; externalLoop test loops back the line to the far end; payloadLoop test only loops back the payload data received from the incoming line; Note that localLoop, remoteLoop and payloadLoop are not supported by all function processors.

mscLpIlsFwdrTestFrmSize.name: mscLpIlsFwdrTestFrmSize
mscLpIlsFwdrTestFrmSize.description: This attribute defines the size of the test data frames in number of bytes.

mscLpIlsFwdrTestDuration.name: mscLpIlsFwdrTestDuration
mscLpIlsFwdrTestDuration.description: This attribute is the duration (in minutes) that test data will be transmitted. In the case of an externalLoop, this is the time that the loop is in effect. Note that dataStartDelay does not apply to the externalLoop.

mscLpIlsFwdrTestResultsTable.name: mscLpIlsFwdrTestResultsTable
mscLpIlsFwdrTestResultsTable.description: This group contains all the statistics related attributes of the Test component.

mscLpIlsFwdrTestElapsedTime.name: mscLpIlsFwdrTestElapsedTime
mscLpIlsFwdrTestElapsedTime.description: This attribute is the number of minutes elapsed since the test started for an externalLoop test. For a data test, this is the time since test data was first transmitted.

mscLpIlsFwdrTestTimeRemaining.name: mscLpIlsFwdrTestTimeRemaining
mscLpIlsFwdrTestTimeRemaining.description: This attribute is the number of minutes remaining before the test is to be stopped according to the duration attribute.

mscLpIlsFwdrTestCauseOfTermination.name: mscLpIlsFwdrTestCauseOfTermination
mscLpIlsFwdrTestCauseOfTermination.description: This attribute records the reason the test is terminated.

mscLpIlsFwdrTestFrmTx.name: mscLpIlsFwdrTestFrmTx
mscLpIlsFwdrTestFrmTx.description: This attribute is the total number of frames sent during the test period. This counter is not expected to reach its maximum value.

mscLpIlsFwdrTestBitsTx.name: mscLpIlsFwdrTestBitsTx
mscLpIlsFwdrTestBitsTx.description: This attribute is the total number of bits sent during the test period. This counter is not expected to reach its maximum value.

mscLpIlsFwdrTestFrmRx.name: mscLpIlsFwdrTestFrmRx
mscLpIlsFwdrTestFrmRx.description: This attribute is the total number of frames received during the test period. This counter is not expected to reach its maximum value. The counter will wrap around to 0 if it does reach its maximum value.

mscLpIlsFwdrTestBitsRx.name: mscLpIlsFwdrTestBitsRx
mscLpIlsFwdrTestBitsRx.description: This attribute is the total number of bits received during the test period. This counter is not expected to reach its maximum value. The counter will wrap around to 0 if it does reach its maximum value.

mscLpIlsFwdrTestErroredFrmRx.name: mscLpIlsFwdrTestErroredFrmRx
mscLpIlsFwdrTestErroredFrmRx.description: This attribute is the total number of errored frames received during the test period. This counter is not expected to reach its maximum value. The counter will wrap around to 0 if it does reach its maximum value.

mscLpEth100CustomerIdentifier.name: mscLpEth100CustomerIdentifier
mscLpEth100CustomerIdentifier.description: This attribute holds the Customer Identifier (CID). Every component has a CID. If a component has a cid attribute, the component's CID is the provisioned value of that attribute; otherwise the component inherits the CID of its parent. The top- level component has a CID of 0. Every operator session also has a CID, which is the CID provisioned for the operator's user ID. An operator will see only the stream data for components having a matching CID. Also, the operator will be allowed to issue commands for only those components which have a matching CID. An operator CID of 0 is used to identify the Network Manager (referred to as 'NetMan' in DPN). This CID matches the CID of any component. Values 1 to 8191 inclusive (equivalent to 'basic CIDs' in DPN) may be assigned to specific customers.

mscLpEth100IfAdminStatus.name: mscLpEth100IfAdminStatus
mscLpEth100IfAdminStatus.description: The desired state of the interface. The up state indicates the interface is operational. The down state indicates the interface is not operational. The testing state indicates that no operational packets can be passed.

mscLpEth100IfIndex.name: mscLpEth100IfIndex
mscLpEth100IfIndex.description: This is the index for the IfEntry. Its value is automatically initialized during the provisioning process.

mscLpEth100ProvTable.name: mscLpEth100ProvTable
mscLpEth100ProvTable.description: This group contains the provisionable attributes of the Eth100BaseT component.

mscLpEth100DuplexMode.name: mscLpEth100DuplexMode
mscLpEth100DuplexMode.description: This attribute specifies the duplex mode of the port. This attribute is ignored if auto negotiation is successful.

mscLpEth100LineSpeed.name: mscLpEth100LineSpeed
mscLpEth100LineSpeed.description: This attribute sets the operating speed for the Ethernet 100BaseT port. This attribute is ignored if auto negotiation is successful.

mscLpEth100AutoNegotiation.name: mscLpEth100AutoNegotiation
mscLpEth100AutoNegotiation.description: This attribute is used to select whether or not the port does auto negotiation. The provisionable values of duplexMode and lineSpeed are ignored if auto negotiation is successful. Refer to the operational attribute autoNegStatus for auto negotiation results.

mscLpEth100ApplicationFramerName.name: mscLpEth100ApplicationFramerName
mscLpEth100ApplicationFramerName.description: This attribute contains the component name of a Framer which is associated with the Eth100BaseT component. This defines which Lan Application will be using this Eth100BaseT interface.

mscLpEth100AdminInfoTable.name: mscLpEth100AdminInfoTable
mscLpEth100AdminInfoTable.description: This group contains the attributes pertaining to the vendor of the equipment.

mscLpEth100Vendor.name: mscLpEth100Vendor
mscLpEth100Vendor.description: This is the name of the vendor supplying the facility.

mscLpEth100CommentText.name: mscLpEth100CommentText
mscLpEth100CommentText.description: Any miscellaneous text about the facility.

mscLpEth100StateTable.name: mscLpEth100StateTable
mscLpEth100StateTable.description: This group contains the three OSI State attributes. The descriptions generically indicate what each state attribute implies about the component. Note that not all the values and state combinations described here are supported by every component which uses this group. For component-specific information and the valid state combinations, refer to NTP 241-7001-150, Passport Operations and Maintenance Guide.

mscLpEth100AdminState.name: mscLpEth100AdminState
mscLpEth100AdminState.description: This attribute indicates the OSI Administrative State of the component. The value locked indicates that the component is administratively prohibited from providing services for its users. A Lock or Lock - force command has been previously issued for this component. When the value is locked, the value of usageState must be idle. The value shuttingDown indicates that the component is administratively permitted to provide service to its existing users only. A Lock command was issued against the component and it is in the process of shutting down. The value unlocked indicates that the component is administratively permitted to provide services for its users. To enter this state, issue an Unlock command to this component.

mscLpEth100OperationalState.name: mscLpEth100OperationalState
mscLpEth100OperationalState.description: This attribute indicates the OSI Operational State of the component. The value enabled indicates that the component is available for operation. Note that if adminState is locked, it would still not be providing service. The value disabled indicates that the component is not available for operation. For example, something is wrong with the component itself, or with another component on which this one depends. If the value is disabled, the usageState must be idle.

mscLpEth100UsageState.name: mscLpEth100UsageState
mscLpEth100UsageState.description: This attribute indicates the OSI Usage State of the component. The value idle indicates that the component is not currently in use. The value active indicates that the component is in use and has spare capacity to provide for additional users. The value busy indicates that the component is in use and has no spare operating capacity for additional users at this time.

mscLpEth100OperStatusTable.name: mscLpEth100OperStatusTable
mscLpEth100OperStatusTable.description: This group includes the Operational Status attribute. This attribute defines the current operational state of this component.

mscLpEth100SnmpOperStatus.name: mscLpEth100SnmpOperStatus
mscLpEth100SnmpOperStatus.description: The current state of the interface. The up state indicates the interface is operational and capable of forwarding packets. The down state indicates the interface is not operational, thus unable to forward packets. testing state indicates that no operational packets can be passed.

mscLpEth100OperTable.name: mscLpEth100OperTable
mscLpEth100OperTable.description: This group contains the Port operational attributes of the Eth100BaseT component.

mscLpEth100MacAddress.name: mscLpEth100MacAddress
mscLpEth100MacAddress.description: This attribute indicates the medium access controller (MAC) address. The MAC address is displayed in canonical format.

mscLpEth100AutoNegStatus.name: mscLpEth100AutoNegStatus
mscLpEth100AutoNegStatus.description: This attribute displays the status of the auto negotiation at the Phy level.

mscLpEth100ActualLineSpeed.name: mscLpEth100ActualLineSpeed
mscLpEth100ActualLineSpeed.description: This attribute indicates the line speed of the Eth100BaseT port.

mscLpEth100ActualDuplexMode.name: mscLpEth100ActualDuplexMode
mscLpEth100ActualDuplexMode.description: This attribute indicates whether the hardware is in half duplex or full duplex mode.

mscLpEth100Eth100StatsTable.name: mscLpEth100Eth100StatsTable
mscLpEth100Eth100StatsTable.description: This group contains the statistical attributes for the Eth100BaseT component.

mscLpEth100FramesTransmittedOk.name: mscLpEth100FramesTransmittedOk
mscLpEth100FramesTransmittedOk.description: This attribute counts the number of frames which were transmitted without errors. This counter wraps to zero after it reaches its maximum value.

mscLpEth100FramesReceivedOk.name: mscLpEth100FramesReceivedOk
mscLpEth100FramesReceivedOk.description: This attribute counts the number of frames which were received without errors. This counter wraps to zero after it reaches its maximum value.

mscLpEth100OctetsTransmittedOk.name: mscLpEth100OctetsTransmittedOk
mscLpEth100OctetsTransmittedOk.description: This attribute counts the number of octets which were transmitted without errors. This counter wraps to zero after it reaches its maximum value.

mscLpEth100OctetsReceivedOk.name: mscLpEth100OctetsReceivedOk
mscLpEth100OctetsReceivedOk.description: This attribute counts the number of octets which were received without errors. This counter wraps to zero after it reaches its maximum value.

mscLpEth100UndersizeFrames.name: mscLpEth100UndersizeFrames
mscLpEth100UndersizeFrames.description: This attribute counts the number of frames that were received but were less than the minimum size (64 bytes). This counter wraps to zero after it reaches its maximum value.

mscLpEth100ReceivedOctetsIntoRouterBr.name: mscLpEth100ReceivedOctetsIntoRouterBr
mscLpEth100ReceivedOctetsIntoRouterBr.description: This attribute counts the number of octets that were not hardware switched but were passed the Router or Bridge software. This counter wraps to zero after it reaches its maximum value.

mscLpEth100ReceivedFramesIntoRouterBr.name: mscLpEth100ReceivedFramesIntoRouterBr
mscLpEth100ReceivedFramesIntoRouterBr.description: This attribute counts the number of frames which were not hardware switched but were passed to the Router or Bridge software. This counter wraps to zero after it reaches its maximum value.

mscLpEth100StatsTable.name: mscLpEth100StatsTable
mscLpEth100StatsTable.description: This group contains statistical attributes for the Ethernet component.

mscLpEth100AlignmentErrors.name: mscLpEth100AlignmentErrors
mscLpEth100AlignmentErrors.description: The alignmentErrors counter indicates the number of frames received which were not an integral number of octets in length. Frames will be checked for alignmentErrors before they are checked for Frame Check Sequence (FCS) errors. If there is an alignment error, the error will only be counted here and not in fcsErrors. This counter wraps around after it exceeds its maximum value.

mscLpEth100FcsErrors.name: mscLpEth100FcsErrors
mscLpEth100FcsErrors.description: The fcsErrors, Frame Check Sequence (FCS) error, counter indicates the number of frames received which were an integral number of octets in length and did not pass the FCS check. This counter wraps around after it exceeds its maximum value.

mscLpEth100SingleCollisionFrames.name: mscLpEth100SingleCollisionFrames
mscLpEth100SingleCollisionFrames.description: The singleCollisionFrames counter indicates the number of frames successfully transmitted which experienced exactly one collision. This counter wraps around after it exceeds its maximum value.

mscLpEth100MultipleCollisionFrames.name: mscLpEth100MultipleCollisionFrames
mscLpEth100MultipleCollisionFrames.description: The multipleCollisionFrames counter indicates the number of frames successfully transmitted which experienced more than one collision. This counter wraps around after it exceeds its maximum value.

mscLpEth100SqeTestErrors.name: mscLpEth100SqeTestErrors
mscLpEth100SqeTestErrors.description: The sqeTestErrors, Signal Quality Error (SQE) Test errors, counter indicates the number of times the 'SQE Test Error' message has been generated for the station. This counter wraps around after it exceeds its maximum value.

mscLpEth100DeferredTransmissions.name: mscLpEth100DeferredTransmissions
mscLpEth100DeferredTransmissions.description: The deferredTransmissions counter indicates the number of frames which experienced a transmission delay because the medium was busy. This counter wraps around after it exceeds its maximum value.

mscLpEth100LateCollisions.name: mscLpEth100LateCollisions
mscLpEth100LateCollisions.description: The lateCollisions counter indicates the number of times a collision was detected later than 512 bit-times into the transmission of a packet. This counter wraps around after it exceeds its maximum value.

mscLpEth100ExcessiveCollisions.name: mscLpEth100ExcessiveCollisions
mscLpEth100ExcessiveCollisions.description: The excessiveCollisions counter indicates the number of frames which failed to get transmitted due to excessive collisions. This counter wraps around after it exceeds its maximum value.

mscLpEth100MacTransmitErrors.name: mscLpEth100MacTransmitErrors
mscLpEth100MacTransmitErrors.description: The Medium Access Controller (MAC) transmit error counter indicates the number of times that a transmission failed due to internal MAC transmit errors. This counter wraps around after it exceeds its maximum value.

mscLpEth100CarrierSenseErrors.name: mscLpEth100CarrierSenseErrors
mscLpEth100CarrierSenseErrors.description: The carrier sense error counter indicates the number of times that the carrier sense condition was lost or never asserted when attempting to transmit a frame. This counter wraps around after it exceeds its maximum value.

mscLpEth100FrameTooLongs.name: mscLpEth100FrameTooLongs
mscLpEth100FrameTooLongs.description: The frame too long counter indicates the number of frames received which exceeded the maximum frame size. This counter wraps around after it exceeds its maximum value.

mscLpEth100MacReceiveErrors.name: mscLpEth100MacReceiveErrors
mscLpEth100MacReceiveErrors.description: The Medium Access Controller (MAC) receive error counter indicates the number of times a receive failed due to internal MAC receive errors. This counter wraps around after it exceeds its maximum value.
